Lynsey Nelson was caught after undercover officials bought her products online and confirmed them to be counterfeit. LONDON - A British woman has been fined after making more than R300,000 selling fake designer goods on Facebook.The 33-year-old was caught selling UGG Boots, designer watches, and sunglasses.Lynsey Nelson was caught after undercover officials bought her products online and confirmed them to be counterfeit.Later arrested for driving without the proper papers, her car was found stuffed with fake designer clothing and sunglasses.Investigations showed Nelson, from Crawley to the south of London, had made more than R300,000 - but was ordered to pay R54,000 and has escaped jail with a four month suspended sentence.(Edited by Neo Koza)